" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fph1665702833385.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fph1665702833385.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fph1665702833385.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fph1665702833385\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                              \n Icon for State\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the icons used to represent the different states of the current tree item type at run time.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fph1665702833385__p_d104768e1_d104769e1_d104770e1\">The <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwb1665702636268.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwb1665702636268.html\" title=\"Determines the behavior of tree items.\">Role (Node)</a> property determines the states the item can have.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fph1665702833385__p_d104771e1_d104772e1_d104773e1\">Select the type of icon (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyph</span> for a Uniface glyph or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Bitmap</span> for any type of supported image file). if you choose, Bitmap, you can also seEnter an image name or select an image.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Tree Item States</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">State</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Condition</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Normal</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Item is not open and not selected.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Selected</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Item is selected in the List View (if specified).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Open</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Node is open in the Tree View, but not selected.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Open and Selected</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fph1665702833385__table_d12371e1_d12372e1_d12373e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Node is open in the Tree View and selected.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fph1665702833385__p_d104774e1_d104775e1_d104776e1\">The icon for Normal state is mandatory. If no other icons are specified, the icon for Normal state is used. If an icon is specified for Normal and for Selected, but not for Open, the Select icon is used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fph1665702833385__p_d104777e1_d104778e1_d104779e1\">For best results, and following the convention used in Microsoft Windows Explorer, use the same icon for Normal and Selected (a closed folder, for example) and another icon for Open and Open/Selected (an open folder, for example).</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"fph1665702833385__note_w179ab1b5c11_w180ab1b5_w181ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The width, height, and color-depth of all icons are determined by the image specified by the Normal icon of the first tree item Type. Any other icon that does not conform to these three values is discarded and will not be used in the widget.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tds1665702636627.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Type</a><p>Determines the role of tree items, and specifies the icons that are used to represent these tree items at run time.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Icon for State Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Icon for State Specify the icons used to represent the different states of the current tree item type at run time. The Role (Node) property determines the states the item can have. Select the type of icon ( Glyph for a Uniface glyph or Bitmap for any type of supported image file). if you choose, Bitmap, you can also seEnter an image name or select an image. Table 1. Tree Item States State Condition Normal Item is not open and not selected. Selected Item is selected in the List View (if specified). Open Node is open in the Tree View, but not selected. Open and Selected Node is open in the Tree View and selected. The icon for Normal state is mandatory. If no other icons are specified, the icon for Normal state is used. If an icon is specified for Normal and for Selected, but not for Open, the Select icon is used. For best results, and following the convention used in Microsoft Windows Explorer, use the same icon for Normal and Selected (a closed folder, for example) and another icon for Open and Open/Selected (an open folder, for example). Note: The width, height, and color-depth of all icons are determined by the image specified by the Normal icon of the first tree item Type. Any other icon that does not conform to these three values is discarded and will not be used in the widget. Related Links Type Determines the role of tree items, and specifies the icons that are used to represent these tree items at run time. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}